<exercise id="fs-idp77964000">
    <problem id="fs-idp47970544"><para id="fs-idm45371920"><link target-id="fig-ch33_03_03" document=""/> When bacteria are destroyed by leuckocytes, pyrogens are released into the blood. Pyrogens reset the body&#8217;s thermostat to a higher temperature, resulting in fever. How might pyrogens cause the body temperature to rise?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-idp83347472"><label/>
    <para id="fs-idp7840544"><link target-id="fig-ch33_03_03" document=""/> Pyrogens increase body temperature by causing the blood vessels to constrict, inducing shivering, and stopping sweat glands from secreting fluid.</para>
</solution>
