        <glossary>
<definition id="fs-idp61580400"><term>acclimatization</term> <meaning id="fs-idp69368736">alteration in a body system in response to environmental change</meaning></definition>
            <definition id="fs-idm77436128"><term>alteration</term> <meaning id="fs-idp26910896">change of the set point in a homeostatic system</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idm24291328"><term>homeostasis</term> <meaning id="fs-idp177332624">dynamic equilibrium maintaining appropriate body functions</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idp157501232"><term>negative feedback loop</term> <meaning id="fs-idm81811136">feedback to a control mechanism that increases or decreases a stimulus instead of maintaining it</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idm70352736"><term>positive feedback loop</term> <meaning id="fs-idm13283424">feedback to a control mechanism that continues the direction of a stimulus</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idp115200272"><term>set point</term> <meaning id="fs-idp3410928">midpoint or target point in homeostasis</meaning></definition>
<definition id="fs-idm98325600"><term>thermoregulation</term> <meaning id="fs-idm16485136">regulation of body temperature</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
